The paper deals with the construction and lower bounds of constant-composition codes, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The use of residue polynomials suggests a connection to algebraic coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses lower bounds and maximal sizes, which are related to computational complexity (cs.CR) and optimization (cs.SI).
